So I have the following plan:

#### 1. Create Enum mixin

```python
class XSOEnum:
    def __init__(self, namespace, localname):
        super().__init__()
        self.xso_class = self._create_class((namespace, localname))

    def _create_name(self):
        return "".join(map(str.title, self.name.split("_"))),

    def _create_class(self):
        return aioxmpp.xso.model.XMLStreamClass(
            self._create_name(),
            (aioxmpp.xso.XSO,),
            {
                "TAG": self.value,
                "__qualname__": ...,
                "enum_member": self,
            },
        )

# example use

class ErrorCondition(XSOEnum):
    BAD_REQUEST = (namespaces.stanzas, "bad-request")
    ...
```

#### 2. Create helper function to create xso.Child descriptors

* Takes XSOEnum
* Creates xso.Child descriptor which accepts all the member.xso_class children

#### 3. Use simple wrapper properties to make access easier

```python
class Error(xso.XSO):
    condition_object = xso.child_xso_enum_helper(ErrorCondition)

    @condition
    def condition(self):
        if self.condition_object is None:
            return None
        return self.condition_object.enum_member

    @condition.setter
    def condition(self, value):
        if self.condition == value:
            return
        self.condition_object = value.xso_class()
```

#### Benefit

* Monkey patching allows to add payloads
* Access to the enum value is still simple

Environment variables are not directly set on container configuration level. Instead they can be set under ``create_options``. In your example, it would look like this:
```
'db': { # Configure container creation and startup
    'image': 'postgres:9.4.4',
    'exposes': {
        5432: 5432
    },
    'binds': ['dbdata', "dbinit"],
    'create_options': {
        'environment': {
            "PGDATA": "/dbdata"
        }
    },
},
```

Same goes for any other option that is defined in [docker-py's docs on the create_container command](http://docker-py.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api/#create_container). Additional options for [HostConfig](http://docker-py.readthedocs.org/en/latest/hostconfig/) such as the ``restart_policy`` can be defined in ``host_config``.

