The whole thing with `_trait_notifiers` and `_trait_validators` was that when I implemented `instance_requires` I wasn't able to write the following:

```python
class TraitType(BaseDescriptor):

    instance_requires = {'_trait_values': dict}
    # ...

class ObserveHandler(BaseDescriptor):

    instance_requires = {'_trait_notifiers': dict}
    # ...

class ValidateHandler(BaseDescriptor):

    instance_requires = {'_trait_validators': dict}
    # ...
```

It just seemed structurally odd that `_trait_notifiers` and `_trait_validators` needed to be expressed as requirements for the both handlers and for `TraitType`.

Again, just something I noticed and it got me thinking.

